this is about to be the longest caption i’ve ever written: 

3 years ago, sara and i got the keys to our very own apartment in Miami beach. We both met in middle school, we weren’t very close but we knew of each other. At the time, Sara was trying to move out and I coincidentally was too so we decided to just move in together. 2020 was an insane year for the entire world, but it was also a life changing year for the both of us. It was like having to learn how to live life all over again. We were financially independent at this point, but with the pandemic and rent, there were a lot of cup noodles and long nights involved but i kid you not, that year was full of growth and self discovery. I can’t confidently say we left that apartment knowing who we were but we definitely knew who we wanted to become. Sara quit her full time job to become a stylist in NYC and I went on to pursue my decorating career. I guess moving into this apartment, even though we could barely afford the rent at the time, was totally worth it. 

In 2020 we started thrifting and hand-making clothes & surprisingly people online were interested in buying these pieces so this is when Peachtree was born! A sustainable place to shop cute & trendy items that can be high quality & a reasonable price. The more we shopped sustainably, the more we learned about how the fast fashion industry is killing our planet. So we made a pact to stop supporting fast fashion brands and now 3 years later, we’re here at this very moment, opening a vintage & second hand clothing store.. together in MIAMI!

Fast fashion’s impact on the planet is immense! 100 billion garments are produced each year and 92 million tonnes get thrown away to landfills. So why produce more clothes when there’s already so much?🥺 we want to make sustainable shopping more accessible to everyone and obviously expand the art & clothing community in Miami! 

i'm so excited to share our passion for clothing with you guys. stay tuned for more information about our grand opening! 💖 @peachtreerevival

just because you feel stuck or unhappy in the moment, doesn’t mean you’ll feel like that forever. we’re always evolving & experiencing new things & thats the most beautiful part of it all. you need to step out of our comfort zone, experience new things, visit new places, and do the things that bring you joy. it’s during the most unexpected moments that you find what’s meant for you.

Announcement!! 🫶 we have been working on this for months now and we finally get to talk to you guys about what we’ve been up to 🥰 

We created a traveling podcast show called “Accidental Experts” where we talk with creatives who’ve landed their dream jobs. Creatives who didn’t know they’d end up where they are, or maybe don’t have conventional backgrounds yet somehow ended up doing things most people only DREAM about. We talk about all the tea, good & bad, of being in the creative industry! 

We both ended up in the design world by ~accident~ just because it was our passion, neither of us went to school for this and we definitely went through unconventional paths to get here. We hope our show can be inspiring for those that want to follow their passion but don’t know where to start. There is no set path you have to take to end up doing what you love ❤️

We’re so excited to release all of the insanely talented and cool people we’ve interviewed around the country so far! and we also have solo episodes, just talking to each other and discussing the ins and outs of our own stories, failures, social media and design careers! 

Here are some behind the scenes…and BY THE WAY- It’s all recorded for YouTube because we’re obviously ~visual people~ and we get to show off the cool creative spaces of our guests!!

The Accidental Experts trailer releases next week Wednesday on July 5th wherever you podcast! Spotify, Apple music, Youtube (DanixTay channel) and full episodes will be live starting July 12th! excited for you all to listen!!

💋 Dani x Tay

💫MAJOR NEWS ALERT💫 I created my very own decor line and it will be available August 1st!!!! i have been dying to tell you guys about this and i don’t know how i kept it a secret for so long! 🥹

as an interior decorator, having the opportunity to create my own decor line means the world to me! We put so much thought and love into creating this collection which was inspired by all my past interior design projects that you all have been so supportive on. Creating this line has allowed me to express my love for design, while also making a positive impact on the world. Ensuring that everything in my line is made ethically and sustainably using organic materials- which is one of the many reasons i collaborated with @yayaandco all the items in my line are proudly handmade in India by courageous women who have bravely escaped from challenging circumstances. Yaya created a safe space where they can freely make fair wages that surpass the living standards, allowing them to rebuild their lives. 

I always dreamt of creating my own decor line but the fact that i can now do that, as well as contribute to a healthier planet, promote fair labor conditions, and provide my clients with beautiful, eco-friendly options that align with their values is something truly surreal.

i hope you guys love these pieces as much as i do!!! there are lots of other designs, like keychains, rugs, pillows & a cute little tote that i’ll be revealing this week so stay tuned! The Dani Klaric collection will be live August 1st 🎀

I am so happy to be able to share a little part of my creativity with you guys. this is not just home decor, this is a dream i’ve had since the day i decided to peruse being an interior decorator. i wanted to create something that represents my style and my mission in this world. partnering w @yayaandco has been a dream come true, not only because they are one of the most authentic and amazing group of people that i’ve met but because their vision aligns with mine. to bring joy and color into peoples homes in a sustainable and ethical way while helping others and the planet. most of the products we created are handmade, by women in India whom we provide a safe working environment where they can make above a living wage. We also only use high quality organic, sustainably sourced and recycled materials to lessen our environmental impact and so these pieces can last a lifetime.
